Today marked our final day with Adam, and it was a powerful conclusion to an insightful week. We took time to reinforce the key lessons we had learned, reflecting on the knowledge and strategies we had developed.

We began the class with a thought-provoking discussion: If I were to be part of a team, what qualities would I want my teammates to have? This exercise encouraged us to consider the essential traits that contribute to a high-performing team—qualities like communication, resilience, adaptability, problem-solving, and accountability. It was a great reminder that success in any challenging endeavor depends not only on individual skill but also on how well a team collaborates and supports one another.

Later, we put these ideas into action through teamwork in the Space Team game, where we had to work together to outsmart and outperform other teams. This activity was both engaging and insightful, as it required quick thinking, cooperation, and trust in our teammates. It reinforced the importance of clear communication and strategic decision-making under pressure—both of which are essential for real-world success.

As our time with Adam came to an end, I felt grateful for the lessons learned and the challenges that pushed me to think differently. This week has provided me with valuable insights that I will carry forward, not just in this program but in future collaborative efforts as well.
